{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bc460a62-b18a-4b3c-8f0e-0c71f8f993fd","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b7936e36-d883-4e35-9c91-961d6fabdb14","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"340E:BD1D2:CBA1AC:EC56C9:69F40142"},"id":"21fabcd7-b658-4168-97c9-c73038b3b489","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:26:31.662Z","parentId":"af70adf0-fe93-46e1-a3b1-510e7110a7f7"}
